HOUSE BILL 620
By Eldridge
SENATE BILL 981
By Southerland
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 2,
Chapter 3, Part 3, relative to convenience voting.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-3-302(f), is amended by adding the
following new subdivision (6):
(6) A county having a population of not less than sixty-four thousand four
hundred (64,400) nor more than sixty-four thousand five hundred (64,500), according to
the 2020 federal census or a subsequent federal census;
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
